title: Time (Tell Me Why #107)(gnv64)
description:
Time: From Ticks to Centuries (Tell Me Why #107)
by Manorama
Manorama | August 2015 | PDF | 98 pages | 14.6 mb
scanned to PDF by me.

Keep your eyes on the clock and watch its hands move - it never stops to think, and its ticking never falters. Yes, time never stops, and all our lives are but a journey through the relentless ticks of time.
What is time? How do we measure it? Can we manipulate it? Such questions have attracted the attention of scientists, philosophers and writers through thousands of years.
Throughout life, we are all traveling a one-way path through time, heading to the future. But can we take a turn and move backwards in time? Or, can we take a double-leap and take a peep into the future? Such thoughts on time have always fired Man's imagination, giving birth to thousands of time-travel stories.
This issue of Tell Me Why gives you an insight into the various aspects of time.
